race.comment: EMERY (4) improved showing at her second run back when launching late for a sound third over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Desperate for this trip now and ready to peak with the key jockey change.  EVERYBODY RISE (1) consistent twelve-start Maiden with his hoof on the till. Shouldered the 60kg when a tough on-pace second over the 1300m at Hawkesbury in fast time. Gets map favours and finds an easier contest with fitness on his side. MOANA GOLD (11) resumes with a host of gear changes and now in the Kristen Buchanan yard. Only had the five starts in Queensland and fitted with the two trials. Well drawn with leading rider booked. REVERBERATES (13) returns from a lengthy break. Cross-over nose band goes on and given the one 900m trial. Slim place contender.
